  "texts": [
    "In a typical soft lithography process, an elastomeric stamp is obtained by molding from a template with the metasurface design and brought into conformal contact with a photoresistcoated substrate.",
    "Via mechanical pressure or solvent interactions, the metasurface designs are formed on the substrate and subsequent pattern transfer steps such as deposition and etching are used to produce the metasurface devices.",
    "Besides direct improvements in instrumentation and materials, the challenges in nanofabrication of diffractive and metasurface-based free-space optical processors can be resolved in the design process by considering the imperfections in fabrication.",
    "Previously, diffractive networks that are invariant to the scale-, shift, and rotation of input images have been demonstrated by introducing these variations in the training stage 167.",
    "An extension of this approach can tremendously improve the robustness of the free-space optical processor toward the unavoidable misalignments between the layers or other imperfections by including them as random parameters in the training process 82, 90, 168."
  ],
